history.content: If you're only taking those three classes, you should be fine - prior programming and Python experience helps in 61A and 16A covers linear algebra you may have seen before transferring.

I wanted to get some opinions on this course load. I am an incoming transfer student and was advised towards CS 70 & 61A. I am trying to round out my schedule.

edit: some other posts have stated––in so many words––that EE 16A's workload is fairly high.

What tech electives would you recommend in lieu of EE 16A? 

Thanks!
